The paper deals with planarity of graphs and their representations, which falls under computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also discusses the complexity of planarity testing, which is a fundamental problem in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also presents bounds on the number of edges in a planar graph, which is related to graph theory (cs.DM) and combinatorics (cs.GT). Finally, the paper discusses the use of ports to represent vertices, which is related to graph drawing and visualization (cs.SI).
